channel.title: Tizenx 667 trouble
channel.description:
allright so when i opened the source/client ect. there was a readMe,
Put Data in your C: Drive
Add a cache into your data folder(beastpk, extintionx, divinityx, or any 667 cache)
Note: this is a pre-beta source, not everything works, if it doesn't work, fix it.
Note #2: Ignore the errors in the client, they don't do anything as far as I know.
http://gyazo.com/c3b4c6128cedcdc689bc9f248f9c207b || http://gyazo.com/6713cd84c1d5452b66adf98b68b3bf8a
When i added a cache into the data and put it in my C: i get the following error in my cmd: [WorldpacketsDecoder] Missing packet 85, expected size: 2, actual size: 2
[WorldPacketsDecoder] Missing packet 93, expected size: 1, actual size: 1
and the tizenx client is blackscreened, can anyone help me? maybe teamviewer to see for yourself. i need help i'm bad when it comes to code to servers above 317 :palm: Skype: Auro.tyrant
thank you ;D
